<HEADLINE> Allen Cut Above Eye, Leaves Court  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Ray Allen was hit in the head and required two
stitches late in the third quarter of Game 4 of the Milwaukee
Bucks' first-round series with the Indiana Pacers on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   With 1:24 left in the third quarter, Indiana's Jalen Rose
grabbed a rebound and swung his right arm behind him, hitting Allen
squarely above the right eye. Allen dropped to the floor and rolled
around, then stood and walked a few steps before lying down again.
</P>
<P>
   Teammates Mirsad Turkcan and Robert Traylor carried him to the
locker room. Bucks spokesperson Cheri Hanson said Allen received
two stitches on a cut above his eye and would be available to
return to the game.
</P>
<P>
   Milwaukee didn't seem likely to need him. The Bucks, who trailed
2-1 in the best-of-series series, were up 83-60 at the time and led
88-62 after three quarters.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
