<DOCNO> APW20000502.0017 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-02 00:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Helton Homers 3 Times Vs. Expos  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Todd Helton became the sixth player in Colorado
Rockies history to hit three home runs in a game, connecting three
times against the Montreal Expos on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Helton, who has nine multi-homer games in three seasons, hit a
pair of two-run homers off Expos starter Dustin Hermanson and added
a solo shot off Anthony Telford in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
   Helton joined Kevin Elster of the Los Angles Dodgers and
Seattle's Alex Rodriguez as the three players to hit three homers
in a game this season.
</P>
<P>
   Vinny Castilla, now with the Tampa Bay Devil Rays, was the last
Colorado player to go deep three times. He did it last June 5
against Milwaukee at Coors Field.
</P>
</TEXT>
