<HEADLINE> Wall St. Stocks Open Lower  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices opened lower on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average was down 50 points in early
trading. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange held a 3-to-2
lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index was off 29 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index was down 6 points.
</P>
<P>
   Monday's gains on Wall Street were being tested.
</P>
<P>
   One area of concern may be as quarterly report from AT&AMP;T. The
telecom giant's first-quarter profits matched forecasts, but it
also warned of slight sales and profit weakness through the end of
the year.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts said the market is also on guard for news about the
economy.
</P>
<P>
   Reports are due 10 a.m. EDT on March new home sales and Leading
Economic Indicators.
</P>
<P>
   The big numbers on the economy come out on Friday, with the
release of the April unemployment report.
</P>
