<HEADLINE> Drew Carey: No Patience for Benefits  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Drew Carey has had it with star-studded charity
benefits.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have no patience for it,'' he says in the upcoming USA
Weekend magazine. ''People are only there to schmooze, be seen and
have their pictures taken. Just write a (expletive) check and shut
up. That's what I do.''
</P>
<P>
   The comedian and actor has a low tolerance for liars and fakes --
frequent targets of his regular-guy sitcom ''The Drew Carey Show.''
</P>
<P>
   Carey finds dishonesty everywhere. Take Santa Claus.
</P>
<P>
   ''If I had kids, I'd say, 'He's a character. He's a guy in a
fake beard who has a winter job.'''
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of fibs, Carey has a new gig: singing and dancing in
ABC's ''Gepetto,'' a musical focused on the father of literature's
little liar Pinocchio.
</P>
<P>
   Says his co-star, Julia Louis-Dreyfus: ''The guy can hoof!''
</P>
