country to qualify for millions of dollars in debt relief under a
newly enhanced program administered by the World Bank and
International Monetary. However, the East African nation must first
clear a World Bank hurdle before obtaining final approval to
receive $50 million a year in debt relief over the next 26 years.
The bank's board of directors met today to decide whether Uganda
can benefit from the high-profile debt initiative. The IMF board
signed on to the deal yesterday.
</P>
