buyout were ''extremely positive.'' Members of the so-called
Phoenix consortium met with BMW executives in their first round of
talks since the collapse of negotiations last week between BMW and
its preferred buyer, British venture capital firm Alchemy Partners.
BMW warned last week that it would shut down Rover's car operations
if it doesn't find a buyer by the end of the month.
