<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-02 20:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> H&AMP;R Block: Tax Services Up 12 Pct.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- H&AMP;R Block said Tuesday that preliminary
results for this year's tax return season showed revenue from fees
for tax preparation and related services increased 12.3 percent
over last year.
</P>
<P>
   The fees received by company-owned and franchised offices for
the Jan. 1-April 17 period were approximately $1.7 billion.
</P>
<P>
   The number of returns prepared by Block rose 3.6 percent to 15.9
million. In all, counting those who prepared their own returns but
filed them electronically through Block offices, Block said it
served 16.5 million taxpayers during the season.
</P>
<P>
   The company said more than three-quarters of its clients chose
electronic filing, a 13 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
   Block said its average fee per client served was $105.98, up
from $96.11 last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
