<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-02 21:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Florio's mother, Lillian, dead at 82  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) -- Lillian Hazel Florio, mother of former
governor and current U.S. Senate candidate Jim Florio, died early
Tuesday. She was 82.
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Florio died at a southern New Jersey nursing home where she
had spent recent years. Arrangements and a cause of death were not
released. Her husband, Vincenzo Florio, whom she married in 1936,
died several years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Florio canceled campaign events Tuesday, and his campaign staff
said a family memorial service would be conducted in private.
</P>
<P>
   In a campaign news release, Florio praised his mother as
''gracious and strong-willed,'' adding he and his brother, Richard,
would miss her and her droll sense of humor.
</P>
<P>
   Florio has frequently cited his mother on the campaign trial
when questioned about his 1990 tax increases, saying the extra
revenue was needed ''to pay the bills,'' a value he learned from
Lillian Florio during his working-class upbringing in Brooklyn.
</P>
<P>
   ''The rent money would go in the coffee can on the shelf, the
Chase &AMP; Sanborn coffee can, because she said you gotta pay your
bills,'' Florio said at a recent appearance. ''It was her value
system, and it is my value system.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-05-02-00 2101 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000502.0206 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-02 21:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sen. Kennedy Talks About His Grief  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- Sen. Edward M. Kennedy says he doesn't believe in
the curse of the Kennedy family.
</P>
<P>
   ''No, that's not the way we've been,'' Kennedy said when asked
about the curse in an interview taped for CBS' ''60 Minutes II,'
airing Tuesday night. '' ... I've been very, very fortunate and
very lucky.''
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy, D-Mass., talked about his grief over the death of his
nephew John F. Kennedy Jr., who died when his plane crashed in
July.
</P>
<P>
   After the crash off the coast of Martha's Vineyard, it once
again fell upon Edward Kennedy, whose brothers President John F.
Kennedy and Sen. Robert F. Kennedy were assassinated, to lead the
family in grief.
</P>
<P>
   ''The prayers, the notes make a great deal of difference to
me,'' Kennedy said. ''And they did last summer. I suppose I don't
do as well as maybe others in being able to sort of talk about
those inner feelings and emotions that have been very close to my
... heart and soul.''
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy's niece and John F. Kennedy Jr.'s sister, Caroline
Kennedy, said the public Kennedy is different from the one the
family knows.
</P>
<P>
   ''I guess it's hard for me to realize that people don't see
Teddy the way that we in our family do.''
</P>
<P>
   ''Nobody was more amazing than Teddy last summer,'' she said.
''If there was anything that came out of that, I think it was a
kind of appreciation I got for how lucky I am to be in our
family.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-02-00 2101 </TRAILER>
