</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- DePaul swingman Quentin Richardson will forgo his final two
years of eligibility and declare for the NBA draft, a source close to the school
said tonight. Richardson averaged 18.1 points and 9.8 rebounds last season,
leading DePaul to a 21-12 record and the school's first NCAA tournament
appearance since 1992. The Blue Demons lost to Kansas in the first round. A
formal announcement of Richardson's decision will be made tomorrow.
</P>
